        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/f4b2a3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2024-03-02T20:31:13.465Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This, much like the ability to mute chats except for @, feels like only a temporary solution to the main issue. This feature appears to work per app, either for all notifications from that app, or certain notifications marked as conversations, not really on a per chat level within Signal. This feature will also reset the volume of notifications after an unknown waiting period. ‚ÄúYou have unread notifications.‚Äù will notify once (or based on someone‚Äôs ‚Äúrepeat alerts‚Äù setting) and remain in the notification screen until you want to tap or dismiss it.</p>\n<p>In my opinion, Signal should not be relying on the OS to do this for them, especially since many versions of android will not get this feature for quite some time. They should also not be relying upon the caring users to tell the users that do not care or want it to just work out of the box ‚Äòwhat and where‚Äô the feature is, it can come off to the user as poor design.</p>\n<p>These stopgap choices put strain on those who already barely tolerate Signal as is, and can discourage those who love Signal as they might lose contacts or actively limit themselves from talking so they don‚Äôt annoy other people.</p>\n<p>I appreciate your feedback, nonetheless.</p>",
