        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/f4b2a3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2024-03-02T20:52:05.523Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello!</p>\n<p>Rate-limited / Delayed / Batch-receive / Periodically-muted notifications, from what I can tell, will deliver X amount of notifications in Y second/minutes/hours. What I propose is a single notification sent based on a chat‚Äôs unread status (think the ‚Äúswipe down to filter unread chats‚Äù feature), without regard for how many messages have been sent in the chat. As long as the chat has unread messages equal to or greater than one, a notification will be sent stating ‚ÄúYou have unread notifications.‚Äù</p>",
