        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/9fc29f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-04-22T15:24:24.454Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I manage several groups with dozens of members and have received multiple requests/lamentations regarding this notification functionality.</p>\n<p>However  I believe that this feature request has been very poorly worded, and that likely has consequences for community and developer engagement. Here is the request carefully restated as a single sentence in order to communicate this desired change and its utility in as few words as possible. This text should much more cleanly make it through machine translation to any language other than English, and I hope it proves helpful:</p>\n<p><em>Please allow for users to receive only one single notification per group when its status changes from Read to Unread, with <strong>no</strong> subsequent notifications for additional messages received in that group until it has changed back from Unread to Read.</em></p>",
